# Frontend Conventions

## Components

- Functional components only; `React.forwardRef` when forwarding refs
- Compound components for complex UI (e.g. `ZoomCard` + `ZoomCardHeader`)
- Custom hooks in `hooks/` for reusable stateful logic
- shadcn/ui + Base UI as base primitives; extend with `zoom-*` components for branding

## Styling

- Tailwind v4 CSS-first config lives in `app/globals.css` — no `tailwind.config.js`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Use CVA (`class-variance-authority`) for components with multiple variants

## Next.js App Router

- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only for interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs
- Path aliases: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks`
- No Pages Router — App Router only
